{
  "stem": "27340.2",
  "chunk_idx": 12,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 9.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "What I think might be of interest to you, and I'd like to come back again to the concentration camp period, if I may-- the reason why, in fact, Goring suddenly decided that he wanted to, uh, release all those who fought in the First World War was that when he himself was a fighter pilot with the Luftwaffe in the First World War.",
      "word_count": 64
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And I think he had about 18 kills to his credit.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "He was in serious difficulty by a French pilot who started following him and shooting at him, and then certainly damaged his aircraft.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And one of Goring's squadron colleagues, another Luftwaffe pilot, managed to eliminate the Frenchmen so that Goring could sort of crash land, as it were, in peace and quiet.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "You've got to remember, in those days, aircraft were flying at fantastic speeds of about 60 or 65 miles per hour.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "They weren't at a fantastic height.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "The impact, of course, was considerable.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "But nevertheless, the planes usually fell into bits and pieces.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And if you were really lucky, you managed to crawl out of the debris, which Goring did.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "Now, he quite clearly was very grateful to his squadron mate for having saved his life.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And it so happened that he was Jewish.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And so Goring literally owed his life to this Jewish colleague of his.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "This Jewish colleague, who oddly enough, also lived in Breslau and was an acquaintance of my grandfather, was approached by Goring in 1934 or '35 and offered a very senior post in the German Luftwaffe.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And although he was Jewish, he accepted this with great honor and was perhaps the only Jew who served in the Luftwaffe.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "He had the rank of an air marshal, General der Flieger, as the Germans call the rank.",
      "word_count": 17
    }
  ],
